IRS990.MissionDesc: TO FACILITATE THE REHABILITATION OF HEALTHCARE PROFESSIONALS WHO HAVE PHYSICAL OR MENTAL CONDITIONS THAT COULD COMPROMISE PATIENT SAFETY AND TO MONITOR THEIR RECOVERY.
IRS990.Desc: WPHP FACILITATED REHABILITATION AND PROVIDED MONITORING SERVICES FOR 239 PHYSICIANS AND OTHER HEALTH CARE PRACTITIONERS WHO HAVE PHYSICAL OR MENTAL CONDITIONS THAT COULD COMPROMISE PATIENT SAFETY. WPHP RECEIVED AND EVALUATED 126 REFERRALS, ADMITTED 60 PARTICIPANTS INTO THE PROGRAM, AND DISCHARGED 66 PARTICIPANTS DURING 2021. WPHP PROVIDED 51 EDUCATIONAL PRESENTATIONS TO APPROXIMATELY 3,433 HEALTH CARE PRACTITIONERS ON THE TOPIC OF PHYSICIAN HEALTH DURING 2021.

Form990ScheduleAPartVIGrp.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: SCHEDULE A, PART III, LINE 12, EXPLANATION OF OTHER INCOME:

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MEETING WITH LEGISLATORS AND STAKEHOLDERS AND PROVIDING TESTIMONY IN FAVOR OF SSB 5496 THAT AMENDS ENABLING LEGISLATION TO ENHANCE PARTICIPANT CONFIDENTIALITY AS WELL AS MODERNIZE AND HARMONIZE LANGUAGE THROUGHOUT.

THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS DESIGNATED FUNDS TO FUNCTION AS ENDOWMENTS (QUASI-ENDOWMENT) TO SUPPORT ITS PARTICIPANTS AS ENVISIONED IN ITS MISSION STATEMENT IN THE EVENT OF SHORTFALLS IN FUNDING OR UNANTICIPATED NEED.

THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE (IRS) HAS DETERMINED THAT WPHP IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAX UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) AND IS CLASSIFIED AS AN ORGANIZATION OTHER THAN A PRIVATE FOUNDATION UNDER SECTION 509(A)(1); ACCORDINGLY, NO PROVISION HAS BEEN MADE FOR FEDERAL INCOME TAX IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. WPHP FILES TAX FILINGS WITH THE U.S., STATE, AND VARIOUS LOCAL GOVERNMENTS. WPHP'S INCOME TAX FILINGS ARE SUBJECT TO EXAMINATION BY VARIOUS TAXING AUTHORITIES. WPHP FOLLOWS THE PROVISIONS OF UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS AS ADDRESSED IN FINANCIAL ACCOUNTING STANDARDS BOARD (FASB) CODIFICATION SUBTOPIC 740-10, INCOME TAXES. WPHP BELIEVES THAT IT HAS APPROPRIATE SUPPORT FOR ANY TAX POSITIONS TAKEN, AND AS SUCH, DOES NOT HAVE ANY UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT ARE MATERIAL TO THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE APPROVAL OF A NEW BOARD MEMBER IS CONTROLLED BY THE WASHINGTON STATE MEDICAL ASSOCIATION. THE BOARD NOMINATES A PERSON FOR THE BOARD, AND THE WASHINGTON STATE MEDICAL ASSOCIATION'S EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE CONFIRMS THE DECISION. THE WASHINGTON STATE MEDICAL ASSOCIATION'S EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE MAY ALSO REMOVE BOARD MEMBER'S AT ANY TIME.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: AMENDMENTS TO THE BYLAWS REQUIRE APPROVAL FROM THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE WASHINGTON STATE MEDICAL ASSOCIATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: PRIOR TO FILING, THE COMPLETED FORM 990 WAS DISTRIBUTED TO EACH BOARD MEMBER FOR REVIEW, COMMENTS, OR QUESTIONS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: BOARD MEMBERS REVIEW THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY ANNUALLY INCLUDING EXAMPLES OF CONFLICTS OF INTEREST. BOARD MEMBERS ARE REQUIRED TO DISCLOSE ANY DIRECT OR INDIRECT FINANCIAL OR PERSONAL INTERESTS THAT POSE POTENTIAL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST AND SIGN A CONFLICT OF INTEREST STATEMENT ANNUALLY. THE SIGNED CONFLICT OF INTEREST FORMS ARE SCANNED, FILED AND STORED IN ACCORDANCE WITH WPHP'S RECORD RETENTION POLICY. COMPLETED AND SIGNED CONFLICT OF INTEREST QUESTIONNAIRES ARE REVIEWED BY THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND/OR THE EXECUTIVE MEDICAL DIRECTOR FOR DISCLOSED ACTUAL OR POTENTIAL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST. NEW ACTUAL OR POTENTIAL CONFLICTS ARE NOT DEFERRED TO ANNUAL DISCLOSURE PROCESS BUT RATHER REPORTED TO THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND/OR THE EXECUTIVE MEDICAL DIRECTOR AS SOON AS THEY ARE IDENTIFIED. THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND/OR EXECUTIVE MEDICAL DIRECTOR DISCLOSE ALL IDENTIFIED ACTUAL OR POTENTIAL CONFLICT OF INTERESTS TO THE WPHP BOARD CHAIR. THE EXECUTIVE MEDICAL DIRECTOR AND EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR EVALUATE CHARITABLE GIVING AND OTHER TYPES OF FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE OFFERED BY COMMERCIAL INTERESTS ON A CASE BY CASE BASIS FOR POTENTIAL CONFLICT OF INTEREST ISSUES. TYPICALLY, SUCH GIVING WILL BE DIRECTED TO THE NAMED SCHOLARSHIP FUNDS AT WPHP CREATED TO ASSIST PARTICIPANTS AND THEIR FAMILIES. ANY QUESTIONS ABOUT THE APPLICATION OF THIS POLICY ARE BROUGHT TO THE ATTENTION OF THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR OR THE EXECUTIVE MEDICAL DIRECTOR.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE COMPENSATION OF THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND EXECUTIVE MEDICAL DIRECTOR IS DETERMINED FROM INFORMATION COMPLIED BY AN INDEPENDENT COMPENSATION CONSULTANT. THIS INFORMATION IS UPDATED ANNUALLY. FROM THESE UPDATES, THE BOARD SETS AND APPROVES EXECUTIVE COMPENSATION FOR THE FOLLOWING YEAR.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: REQUESTS FOR THE GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE EVALUATED ON A CASE BY CASE BASIS.
THE ORGANIZATION'S PROCESS FOR SELECTING AN INDEPENDENT AUDITOR AND FOR OVERSEEING THE FINANCIAL STATEMENT AUDIT DID NOT CHANGE DURING THE YEAR.
